The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 Loss estimate

 New Delhi, Jan. 6: A preliminary assessment by the Centre has put the financial loss in the tsunami disaster in Tamil Nadu, Andhra Pradesh, Kerala and Pondicherry at Rs 5,322 crore. It has yet to come up with details on the loss in the Andaman and Nicobar Islands.

 A home ministry official said initial estimates of the financial loss have been put at Rs 2,730 crore for Tamil Nadu, Rs 720 crore for Andhra Pradesh, Rs 1,358 crore for Kerala and Rs 512 crore for Pondicherry.

 Prime Minister Manmohan Singh had earlier announced an interim relief of Rs 500 crore from the National Calamity Contingency Fund. 




